        Parameters:

      • isUriLetterOrDigit

        public static boolean isUriLetterOrDigit(char c)
        Determines if the supplied character belongs to the group of letters or digits allowed in URI. Allowed letters and digits conform to RFC3986 Unreserved Characters to groups identified as ALPHA and DIGIT. ALPHA is defined as hexadecimal ranges 0x41-0x5A and 0x61-0x7A. DIGIT is defined as hexadecimal range 0x30-0x39.
